Course of practical German designed  for students to  increase their  vocabulary, develop reading comprehension, conversational and listening skills,  and increase grammar skills. Prerequisites for participating: students must have passed the previous course of 160-200 hours and achieved language proficiency corresponding to the requirements of the Council of Europe at level A2. Course is partially web-based. Level of the language proficiency can be determined by a test at the following address: http://www.goethe.de/cgi-bin/einstufungstest/einstufungstest.pl or http://einstufungstests.klett-sprachen.de/einstufung/index.php?questname=daf&questclass=B1.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Objective of the course is to achieve the language proficiency corresponding to the requirements of the Council of Europe at level B1 (Zertifikat Deutsch).Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Course of practical German designed  for students to  increase their  vocabulary.
